    "editor": "Andy Yingst",
    "explanation": "<i>The 1985 movie Clue was released with three different endings, each featuring different guilty parties to the murder of Mr. Boddy.</i><br><br><i>Across</i><br>1. B(LACK + M[otive])AILED<br>9. LO(L.L.)S<br>11. strANGE LAnds<br>13. (CAL[o]RIE)*<br>14. GAVE + [tria]L<br>15. SKIM[p]<br>16. NO SI(excus[E])R<br>17. “SANS A” <i>Sansa is Arya’s sister on Game of Thrones.</i><br>18. (TO REST)*<br>19. [f]INES <i>starting with L, N or S</i><br><br><i><b>—> LINES</i></b><br>21. (HER)< <i>around</i> HAS<br>25. “AS KIN”<br>30. EA. + R.N.<br>31. \\ROUTINE\\ <i>Spoonerism</I><br>32. <i>Ms.</i> SCARLET <i>is one of the suspects in Clue.</i><br>33. L.I. + B(E + R.T.)Y <i>NYC’s E train is the 8 Avenue Local; BY is clued with “via.”</i><br>34. (E-ROT)<br>35. <i>2x def.</i><br>36. SH(r.)OVE<br><br><i><b>—> NINES</b></i><br>21. RAT + EDG[y]<br>25. <i>>2x def.</i><br>30. hOLLAback<br>31. OOMP([tub]A)H <i>&lit.</i><br>32. MR. GREEN <i>is one of the suspects in Clue.</i><br>33. \\SKI MYRRH\\<br>34. <i>2x def.</i><br>35. \\TARA\\<br>36. everY EASTer<br><br><i><b>—> SINES</b></i><br>21. \\NICE\\<br>25. T(dina[R])ILL<br>30. [g]ROAN<br>31. (CHORE)* + E. <I>“E for Everyone” is a video game rating.</I><br>32. <i>Mrs.</i> PEACOCK <i>is one of the suspects in Clue.</i><br>33. ([s]ASSAFRA[s])*<br>34. [d]ASHE[d]<br>35. T.(ODD)Y.<br>36. (SA[m]PLE)*<br><br><i>Down</i><br>1. BESS <i>around</i> L[orelei] <i>As in</i> Porgy & Bess.<br>2. [g]LOCK<br>3. [t]ALLIN[n]<br>4. CLA[i]MS<br>5. <i>2x def.</i><br>6. gANGSTer<br>7. L. + [e]EVEE<br>8. (SLADE)*<br>10. SIN + A.I.<br>12. \\GAITS\\<br><br><i><b>—> LINES</i></b><br>19. L.A.N. + C[ancel] + E.T.<br>20. “EARL-Y”<br>21. RE[v.]ELS<br>22. SatirizE A TITle<br>23. STAR + [hors]E<br>24. \\HERTZ\\<br>26. (TEES)< + O[peration]<br>27. \\QUITO\\<br>28. IN[s.]URE<br><br><i><b>—> NINES</b></i><br>19. (N)EAR[n]ER<br>20. ELM + E.R.<br>21. zoROASTrianism<br>22. [ch.]ALICE<br>23. (GOD)< + MA<br>24. GO + REY <i>Rey is a character from the third</i> Star Wars <i>trilogy.</i><br>26. (ARE + P.O.)<<br>27. (ON AN)<<br>28. G[ive] + HOST<br><br><i><b>—> SINES</b></i><br>19. (SIENA)* + D[ominicans] <i>As in Sinead O’Connor.</i><br>20. THOSE <i>cyc.</i><br>21. \\GRATE\\<br>22. (TOONS)*<br>23. S[paceballs] + CARY <i>Cary Elwes was Robin Hood in Mel Brooks'</i> Men in Tights<i>; Scary Spice is Mel B.</i><br>24. \\SOAK AL\\<br>26. (PACER)<<br>27. (RISK)*<br>28. \\LAY CHE\\ <i>“Leche” is Spanish for “milk.”</i><br>",
